The following subjects shall be administered in the same manner subject to the same limitations and requirements as provided for the Kentucky Employees Retirement System as follows:
Cessation of membership, as provided for by KRS 61.535;
Medical examiners and hearing procedures, as provided for by KRS 61.665;
Actuarial bases, as provided for by KRS 61.670;
Duties of the employer, as provided for by KRS 61.675;
Exemption of benefits of the system for taxation and qualified domestic relations orders, as provided for by KRS 61.690;
Retirement allowance increase, as provided for by KRS 61.691;
Calculation of retirement allowance, as provided for by KRS 61.599;
Beneficiaries to be designated by member, change, rights, as provided for by KRS 61.542;
Year of service credit, as provided for by KRS 61.545;
Refund of contributions, death after retirement, as provided by KRS 61.630;
Custodian of fund, payments made, when, as provided for by KRS 61.660;
Credit for service prior to membership date, as provided for by KRS 61.526;
Member's account, confidential, as provided for by KRS 61.661;
Cessation of membership, loss of benefits, as provided for by KRS 61.550;
Correction of errors in records, as provided for by KRS 61.685;
Maximum disability benefit, as provided for by KRS 61.607;
Retirement application procedure, effective retirement date, as provided for by KRS 61.590;
Employer contributions, as provided for by KRS 61.565;
Reinstatement of lost service credit, purchase of service credit, interest paid, and delayed contribution and installment payments, as provided for by KRS 61.552;
Reciprocal arrangement between systems, as provided by KRS 61.680;
Refund of contributions, conditions, as provided by KRS 61.625;
Hospital and medical insurance plan, as provided by KRS 61.702;
Death benefit, as provided by KRS 61.705;
Disability retirement allowance, reduction, and discontinuance, as provided by KRS 61.615;
Service credit, Armed Forces, as provided by KRS 61.555;
Reinstated employee, contributions on creditable compensation, as provided for by KRS 61.569;
Statement to be made under oath, good faith reliance, as provided for in KRS 61.699;
Retirement of persons in hazardous positions, as provided for by KRS 61.592;
Direct deposit of recipient's retirement allowance as provided in KRS 61.623;
Purchase of service credit effective July 1, 2001, as provided in KRS 61.5525;
Payment of small amounts upon death of member, retiree, or recipient without formal administration of the estate as provided in KRS 61.703;
Suspension of retirement payments on reemployment, reinstatement, recomputation of allowance, waiver of provisions in certain instances, reemployment in a different position, as provided for by KRS 61.637;
Medical examination and financial review after disability retirement, staff review, as provided in KRS 61.610; and
Employer payment of increases in creditable compensation during the last five (5) years of employment as provided by KRS 61.598.
